item.title: North Carolina: Lawmakers could repeal 'bathroom bill'
item.description: North Carolina's controversial "bathroom bill" could be repealed Wednesday after months of intense criticism and economic losses.

item.title: What Geoffrey Garrett is reading this week
item.description: Geoffrey Garrett is the 13th dean of The Wharton School at the University of Pennsylvania.

item.title: Berlin attack: Police hunt Tunisian suspect after finding ID papers in truck
item.description: Police are searching for a Tunisian man in his early 20s in connection with the Berlin Christmas market attack, a German security official told CNN on Wednesday.

item.title: Israel ambassador to US: Move embassy to Jerusalem
item.description: Israeli ambassador to the US Ron Dermer called on the US to move its embassy to Jerusalem, a campaign pledge President-elect Donald Trump has promised to make good on.

item.title: Gingrich: Trump dropping 'drain the swamp'
item.description: "Drain the swamp" was a refrain of Donald Trump's presidential campaign, but Newt Gingrich says the president-elect "doesn't want to use it anymore" now that he's knee deep in swamp water.

item.title: Prince Philip Fast Facts
item.description: View CNN's Fast Fact on Great Britain's Prince Philip (Duke of Edinburgh), husband of Queen Elizabeth II and the great-great grandchild of Queen Victoria.

item.title: Apple AirPods review: Do they actually stay in your ears?
item.description: A look at how the Apple AirPods work in action.

item.title: Sources: Russia tests anti-satellite weapon
item.description: Russia has recently tested what is believed to be an anti-satellite weapon, US sources with knowledge of the test told CNN.

item.title: US returns land its controlled since WWII to Japan amid local anger
item.description: The US military will hand over a 9,909 acres (4,000 hectares) of land to Japan Thursday, in what's lauded as the largest return of US-occupied land since 1972.

item.title: Queen Elizabeth II Fast Facts
item.description: Read CNN's Fast Facts about Queen Elizabeth II and learn more about the Queen of the United Kingdom of Great Britain.

item.title: '80s heartthrob Richard Marx helps subdue unruly airline passenger
item.description: An unruly passenger on an Korean Air flight Tuesday should've known better than to attack the crew with Richard Marx on board. The '80s singer was right there waiting for him -- with rope.

item.title: Ambassador shooting: Russia pushes back on Turkey's Gulenist claim
item.description: The Kremlin has pushed back against Turkey's allegations that a movement led by exiled cleric Fethullah Gulen was behind the assassination of Russia's ambassador to Ankara.

item.title: Snow falls in Sahara for first time in 37 years
item.description: New photos show snow-capped dunes in Algeria's Ain Sefra

item.title: Trump's still going wrong on Twitter
item.description: When the President-elect speaks, people listen -- and governments, businesses and ordinary citizens scramble to parse, interpret and, given his power, make snap decisions about how to act and respond.

item.title: Australian Open lifts prize money to record $36 million
item.description: After being rocked by allegations of match-fixing earlier this year, the Australian Open will be paying players a record total prize money pot of $36 million to combat corruption at the bottom rungs of the sport.

item.title: Trump adds yet another billionaire to his team
item.description: The latest addition to Trump's team of ultra-rich administration officials is Vincent "Vinnie" Viola, a New York businessman and hockey franchise owner who was nominated Monday for secretary of the Army.

item.title: Trump family says it's 'not involved' in conservation fundraiser
item.description: The Trump family is distancing itself from a January 21 fundraising event after press reports that attendees could get a meeting with President Donald Trump for $1 million.

item.title: Bana Alabed: Seven-year-old Syrian girl meets Turkey's President Erdogan
item.description: Bana Alabed, the seven-year-old who brought the plight of Aleppo's victims to the world, met Turkish president Recep Erdogan in Ankara.

item.title: 2016: The year in supercars
item.description: It used be that driving an exotic car meant a sore rear-end and buzzing ears. Thankfully, that is no longer true.

item.title: Lapland: Skiing in the 'home of Santa Claus'
item.description: The FIS World Cup and its skiiers touched down in the town of Levi in Finnish Lapland this year, home to Santa Claus, seven-month winters and the Northern Lights.

item.title: Margot Robbie cheekily confirms relationship status
item.description: Margot Robbie offered a saucy response to speculation that she's gotten married.

item.title: At last there is light on the horizon
item.description: There's a lot going on in the skies above us right now. Today, December 21st marks the winter solstice, where daylight hours start to get longer in the Northern hemisphere.

item.title: Borussia Dortmund: How 'Yellow Wall' boosts soccer stars
item.description: With more than 80,000 fans flooding through the gates every week -- and 25,000 in Europe's largest free standing terrace -- Borussia Dortmund's 'Yellow Wall' gives players a boost.

item.title: NYPD names pot of gold theft suspect
item.description: The man caught on camera stealing a pot of gold in midtown Manhattan last September is Julio Nivelo, a 53-year-old believed to be in the Los Angeles area

item.title: 2016: A tipping point for excitement in self-driving cars
item.description: As the world focused on an election, an industry quietly took off.

item.title: Jack Nicklaus: Is major haul untouchable, even for Tiger Woods?
item.description: He remains the master until Tiger Woods or anyone else proves otherwise, but has Jack Nicklaus already sealed the title of Greatest Of All Time?

item.title: Swedish start-up tackles air pollution head on
item.description: With the help of air filter experts and clothing designers, Airinium have crafted a pollution mask that they believe is both functional and fashionable.

item.title: Turning 50: How to make the most of midlife
item.description: CNN's Kelly Wallace gets advice about turning the big 5-0 from Robi Ludwig, author of a new book about midlife, "Your Best Age is Now."

item.title: Alan Knuckey: Rugby player recreates the incredible trick that went viral
item.description: It's the sort of trick that could make you a hero -- or leave you looking like a bit of a chump. After 15 years of trying, Alan Knuckey finally pulled it off.

item.title: Behind the magical scenes of The English National Ballet's 'Nutcracker'
item.description: Principal dancer Lauretta Summerscales invites CNN Style behind the scenes of festive classic "The Nutcracker," staged by The English National Ballet.
